description:
WHAT IS TO BECOME OF CLARA OSWALD? DOCTOR WHO MAGAZINE PREVIEWS THE AMAZING FINAL EPISODES – IN ISSUE 493!

Doctor Who Magazine looks ahead to the dramatic final episodes of the latest series –Sleep No More, Face the Raven,Heaven Sent and Hell Bent, and talks to to the writers of the episodes: Mark Gatiss, Sarah Dollard and showrunner Steven Moffat. We also catch up with the director of the series finale, Rachel Talalay and the Doctor himself, Peter Capaldi...

“The whole episode’s quite big,” Peter tells DWM of the 12th and final episode of the series, Hell Bent. “It’s huge, actually – but also there’s a sadness, a romance, and a tragedy to Episode 12,” he says. “It’s just so romantic. It’s very effective. And I loved all the stuff on one particular set. I was very excited. It looks so modern – a Kubrick-y kind of vibe. It was very nice. We’re in a very interesting place, because we’re competing with bigger shows, frankly. Most American shows have four times the budget per episode that we have, but that’s what we’re up against. We’re competing with Game of Thrones… This is traditional for Doctor Who, but it goes to show what this amazing production team can achieve.”

ALSO INSIDE ISSUE 493...

  • INSIDE NUMBER 9
    DWM     reunites League of Gentlemen stars Mark Gatiss and Reece Shearsmith – writer and star respectively of Sleep No More – for an exclusive interview! Plus a chat with guest star Bethany Black.
  • BREAKING THE FOURTH WALL
    Showrunner Steven Moffat answers readers’ questions, and reveals just who the Doctor is talking to when he’s looking directly at the camera...
  • IMMORTAL WORDS
    Poll-winning writer Jamie Mathieson discusses his varied career, including his life as a stand-up comedian, and how his latest episode, The Girl Who Died, came to be.
  • HIGHWAY TO HELL
    Writer Catherine Tregenna talks in-depth to DWM about how she came to write her recent Doctor Who episode, The Woman Who Lived.
  • BACK TO LIFE
    Jacqueline Rayner explains why The Girl Who Died reminded her of the Moxx of Balhoon, her childhood and Dodo in Relative Dimensions.
  • TALES OF DARKNESS
    The Doctor and Clara face terror in the cemetery in their latest terrifying comic strip adventure, The Highgate Horror, by Mark Wright, illustrated by David A Roach.
  • THE DWM REVIEW
    DWM reviews The Girl Who Died, The Woman Who Lived, The Zygon Invasion and The Zygon Inversion. Plus, the latest DVDs, books and audios are put under the spotlight.
  • COMING SOON
    All the latest and forthcoming Doctor Who CDs are previewed – including UNIT: Extinction and Jago & Litefoot & Strax!
  • PLUS! All the latest official news, competitions, ratings round-up, Wotcha! and The DWM Crossword.

An exclusive limited edition variant cover will be on sale at the Doctor Who Festival between Friday 13 and Sunday 15 November.

The noose is tightening around Lanfeust and the Magohamoth whilst Lylth, the devourer of worlds, is on their trail!

This album introduces us to a new, strange world and the particularities of its inhabitants, against a backdrop of a suspenseful space-political thriller.

Granite, who thought she’d finally destroyed the monster that Callista had become, sent her vessel through the Gate of the Universe and crashed on

the planet Glèbe. This is a strange world dominated by an insect-like people with highly-advanced technology, and where other intelligent races live, including one very close to mankind. Meanwhile, on Neuhorf, Callista organizes a formidable coup d’état and gets hold of several hundreds of worlds…

description: Rampage Jackson knew doing charity benefits had a cost but little did he or the other celebrities he's with realize that cost could be their lives. Traveling to an island off the coast of Japan, Rampage soon learns that leaked nuclear radiation and superpowered meteor rocks don't mix as he finds himself defending this small crew of do-gooders from a threat so big it may even be too much for Rampage Jackson to handle!
Rampage is hunted in Florida by a powermad, super-scientist and she's bent on getting Rampage's power all for herself.
Rampage travels to New Orleans where a team of scientists have unleashed a powerful threat but in the city of brotherly love he’ll also make a powerful new ally!
Rampage travels through time but soon learns to save the future he’s going to have to fight it!
Rampage travels to Japan to check on an old friend but this leads to an epic battle with ninjas he may not survive!

Rampage travels to Los Angeles where the city is getting an extension to its underground rail line but they’ll dig up something they shouldn’t have and Rampage will be the only hope for the City of Angels!

Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Starting at the height of Archiemania in 1969, Everything's Archie linked with the Archie Saturday morning cartoon and was the home for some of the funniest stories ever produced. In this installment, we share some of the best and most pivotal stories from the history of the series, from The Archies' visit to Filmation Studios to what might have happened if Archie had been drafted into the Army!
name: Everything's Archie

description: The second title from the STATUS QUO...SHATTERED! line that features the Advent Universe's greatest martial artist in his own book. FIST OF THE DRAGON #1 is 70's Style Martial Arts Mayhem in a two-issue miniseries as Dragon searches for the murderer of his teacher but he must first come face-to-face with the world's greatest martial artists in single combat! 24 Full Color Pages

After 3350 years Aten Ra finally reconnects with the reincarnation of his estranged love, Ankesenamun, the women he betrayed and who condemned him to his life of immortal wanderings. After they reminisce about her past lives and are confronted with their future, things aren’t as rosy as either would have liked. Is it back to dad, the world’s greatest terrorist, for Ankesenamun? Mystery, mayhem and misery with beautiful women you can’t trust and creepy men you want to avoid.

Our 10th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly – the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.

description:
The Iron Maiden part 2

Kit and Justice must race to save a princess's throne and stop an evil usurper (like there's any other kind). Not only do they have to get there before the ceremony is complete but the real princess has been infected and her time is also running out. And let's not forget that they haven't been invited and the guys at the door aren't just going to let them in.

So what else is new?
name: The Iron Maiden Part 2

description:
R.U. Pooping?

The reanimated zombie corpse of rockstar R.U. Nixon has begun doing television commercials for the Phredmart chain of retail stores. Bob's mother has befriended the saleswoman that works for Phredmart and Bob's archenemy,-- Mr. Medusa. (Who now thinks that Bob is his father... Because Bob ate him and pooped him out.)
name: R.U. Pooping?

description:
Captives of the Catacombs

Dracula and Thalia may have escaped from the Tower of London, but when they return to Dracula's estate, they're in more danger than ever! Who is the madman that has caged them with a house full of deathtraps, and what does he want from the greatest of all vampires? Find out if Dracula and Thalia can survive becoming Captives of the Catacombs!
name: Captives of the Catacombs

description: Joyce was homeschooled, and these first few weeks of college have been her first foray into public education. But she and her friends are learning that villains are around every corner, from jerky dads to depression and booze to the Whiteboard Dingdong Bandit
name: Amazi-Girl Is Always Prepared For Anything

description:
Dusk - Chapter Two

After the tragic death of her parents, Kaitlyn arrived to live with her sister, Christina, in a city called Dusk. Built on a planet hanging motionless in space, Dusk is a city on the edge of light and dark perpetually frozen at the same time of day.

Kaitlyn and Christina narrowly avoided a mugging thanks to the heroics of

Detective Eddie Hizaki who intervened despite chasing a suspect in a series of apparent kidnappings. After stopping the mugging, Eddie resumed the chase along with his partner Neil Weathers.

Later, at Christina's apartment, Kaitlyn was home alone while her sister was on a job interview. A knock on the door ended up being the man who tried to mug them, determined to get what he came for, Kaitlyn.
name: Chapter Two

description:
Empire of the Gods

Aegis miraculously survived the annihilation of his people and home 100 years ago. Now, he has grown into a strong young God. Aegis wanders through Gaea in search for the Titaness that his father failed to free.
name: Empire of the Gods

description: Puffing tuff with Tiger.

Trouble in the North

Three fighters entered the forest to investigate... During this struggle Chalace and Spaide push beyond conventional methods in power in order to succeed in rescuing the disappeared Scout Master, Yuma. But has the damage been done? Three fighters entered the forest to investigate. Only 2 escaped intact.

Later In town, Sy hears a tale that doesn't seem to relate to what he had already learned in the desert city. Though the similarities between this telling could fit into the story he created; INFINITY. The thought crosses Sy's mind immediately though the link is currently nothing more than a guess. These questions add to this world's mystique as he struggles to make sense of things.

Subject K: Part 4

Subject K learns more about the underground Resistance, which has come under attack by the Pale Man's forces. Spez's condition proves to be more complicated than Dr. Layne initially thought. Subject K decides to set out on his own, with disastrous results. Meanwhile, on Pale Man's station, Dr. Vernon continues her work trying to synthesize Alternium. Pale Man reveals some new sensations as he tries to speed things up in the lab.

description: If you thought Department REBUS was a dangerous place...THINK AGAIN.

Into the vasty deep

With Jack in their sights, Detectives Bergeon and Shelby finally have their killer within their grasp. Fighting to stay one step ahead, both men must race against time to bring Jack to justice.

description: "I prey thee to enter with intent of harm, but to depart without recourse for survival." Shepherd 7:23

Regret

The Earth has changed much since the Super Wizard first came upon our world. Should Stardust try to repair the damage done to our civilization or would that merely risk worse danger? But Stardust doesn't have long to consider this, because his greatest nemesis has survived his long absence and now that the Super Wizard has returned he craves revenge.

description: As the people in Emerald Oaks exposed to "Super Bud" start developing powers, PHAR-T draws closer to finding them. Reggie isn't feeling so well, and Rob is about to find out just how "special" those brownies he made really are.

Join us as young Meg struggles to avoid life as a "Gang Sweetheart." Then a wealthy Plain Jane doubts her suitor's true intentions in "Buy Me That Man." Golden Age Kirby classics, lovingly restored and refreshed!

Escape

As a terrified boy is stalked by a shadow and a drunken misfit is haunted by a reflection, a crippled hero rejects the real world and a lost girl yearns to have it back. Deep underground, in a prison that does not exist, a faceless dead man flexes and iron groans. It's now or never. They must escape.

description: John and Naomi were childhood sweethearts— and then they grew up. Life took them on very different paths, but accidents will happen. When their two lives intersect again, they decide to have another go at love. But this is no simple romantic rekindling: Both John and Naomi are wearing the hairshirts of miserable memories and dark nightmares, which may be too painful to shed, even if they hold each other tight again. Their terrible struggle is powerfully represented in beautifully nuanced art that reflects a soulless city, troubled love, and tense aimlessness.

Jessica Drew debuts as Spider-Woman in her inaugural Marvel Masterworks! Raised within the arms of the terrorist group Hydra, Jessica was taught to see the world from their twisted point of view and became a top agent in their international criminal network. But she began to break the bonds of her indoctrination when she crossed paths with Nick Fury and the Thing, becoming her own woman - and soon, an incomparable Marvel hero! Join us as Jessica Drew sets out to uncover her true origins, her identity and her place in the world. She'll employ both her spider-powers and her spy craft in battles with enemies mystical and macabre - and you'll soon see why Spider-Woman earned a reputation as one of Marvel's most unique series! Collecting MARVEL SPOTLIGHT (1971) #32, MARVEL TWO-IN-ONE #29-33 and SPIDER-WOMAN (1978) #1-8.
